implements Collection<E>, ISearchableByFilter<E>
    This class handles a simple linked list of IContainerElements. It implements the Collection interface and provides implementation for its methods. Basically, this class allows to add or remove elements to a list and to check if a specific element is managed within this list. The specification of the elements is given in the IContainerElement interface.

    In addition, this class also provides an implementation for the ISearchableByFilter interface. This means, that the list can be filtered by an ISearchFilter.

    The Container does not allow insertion of NULL elements.
